# Per-role lab notebooks are append-at-the-top journals: every PR inserts a
# `### <time>` entry under the same top-of-today anchor, so two concurrent
# same-role PRs collide there on merge. `merge=union` is git's built-in
# "keep both sides' lines" driver - it auto-resolves those append conflicts by
# retaining every entry instead of erroring, which is exactly the manual
# resolution the immutable-entries rule already prescribes. No per-clone
# `git config` is needed; the attribute alone activates the built-in driver.
# Ordering is not guaranteed (a concurrent burst may land two entries slightly
# out of time-order), but entries are timestamped and immutable, so that is
# cosmetic. See Issue #1221 (Option B).
research/lab_notebook/*.md merge=union
